commit.message: Merge PR #572

Review of PR #572

- Rename config var CTRL_PTY to COMMAND_PTY to match SvxLink server
- Use similar command parser as in SvxLink server
- Set PTY to be line buffered
- Use the Async::Config::valueUpdated mechanism
- Write command response to PTY

Change reflector config at runtime

Introduce a new branch "reflector-ptyctrl" following an idea from
Jens/DJ1JAY to change some SvxReflector parameters on runtime.
Enable using different effects for trim and maximize
Update link path for retrieving metar info
Reset project version to "master"
Fix wrong filename of README for release 24.02
Backport release 19.09.2
Prepare for release 24.02

Include project version in application version printouts

- The application specific version is now called APP_VERSION
- The project version is called PROJECT_VERSION
- VERSION=APP_VERSION@PROJECT_VERSION

Qtel: Add developer name to AppStream metadata

This is now required by many AppStream parsers
Don't accept monitoring of TG #0
Use "make package" in ubuntu/debian build containers
Fix doc error

Add support for LADSPA audio processing

LADSPA  is  a framework for sharing pluggable audio components and there
are numerous plugins to choose from. SvxLink now support using LADSPA
plugins to shape receiver audio.
Update container build for Debian and Ubuntu

Fix warning/bug in Async::AudioSplitter

Newer versions of g++ warn when there is a possiblility that a negative
size is used in for example the memcpy function. A check was added so
that the given size to memcpy can never be negative.

Newer versions of CMake require ENABLE_EXPORTS

The ENABLE_EXPORTS target property is required by CMake >= 3.5 to enable
plugins to link to symbols in the main executable.
Require minimum cmake 3.5
Require gpiod version 1
Update year in template files
Fix compiler warnings
Fix spelling error
Fix documentation for DTMF_MUTING

Bugfix for the 1750_MUTING configuration variable

Setting the 1750_MUTING configuration variable to 0 did not disable the
feature. The variable had to be commented out.
Add missing include file
Improved docs for the EVENT logic core PTY command
Improved playNumber TCL function

All audio clips are now maximized to a dBFS level of -6 dB

The maximum level of all audio clips are now maximized to a dBFS level
of -6 dB instead of -3 dB. This will better match a standard calibration
done using the devcal utility.

New EVENT command for the logic COMMAND_PTY

Use the EVENT logic PTY command to call any event (TCL function).
